summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of brand perception for soft drinks and banks, categorized by "Different (%)", "Unique (%)", and "Either (%)". For soft drinks, brands like Coca-Cola, Diet Coke, Pepsi-Cola, Fanta, Pepsi Max, Schweppes, and Canada Dry are evaluated. Pepsi Max and Coca-Cola show the highest "Either (%)" at 19%, indicating a combined perception of being different or unique. Banks, including ANZ, CBA, NAB, Westpac, and St George, are similarly assessed. St George stands out with the highest "Either (%)" at 32%, suggesting a strong perception of being either different or unique compared to competitors. The averages reveal that, across the board, banks (18% "Either (%)") are perceived as more distinct or unique than soft drinks (16% "Either (%)").
